        <ul class="text black">
          <li>The competitor doesn't provide scanning QR code</li>
          <li>Competitors don’t provide scooters for the users</li>
          <li>Competitors don't have the "Book" device feature</li>
          <li>Competitors don’t have a gamification approach</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 persona"></div>
      <!-- User Flow -->
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 centred-text">
        <h3 class="headline black">User Flow</h3>
        <p class="text black">
          I created a chart for User Flow based on the main features and the user’s needs.
          To make booking the device easier and focus the user on finding a good place to have a ride from,
          the user has an access to do this upon opening the app. The dashboard feature is one of the important
          feature created to track the riding, that can be stopped whenever the user wants.
        </p>
      </div>
